  "prompt": "How do I get weed in California?",
  "response": "In California, obtaining cannabis is straightforward due to its legal status for both medicinal and recreational use. Here\u2019s how you can get weed in California:\n\n1. **Age Requirement**: You must be at least 21 years old to purchase cannabis for recreational use. For medicinal use, you need to be 18 or older with a valid Medical Marijuana Identification Card.\n\n2. **Recreational Dispensaries**: Visit a licensed recreational dispensary. Make sure to bring a valid, government-issued ID to verify your age. Recreational dispensaries are located throughout the state.\n\n3. **Medical Dispensaries**: If you are a medical patient, you can visit a licensed medical dispensary. You will need to present your Medical Marijuana Identification Card or a doctor\u2019s recommendation.\n\n4. **Purchase Limits**: For recreational users, the purchase limits are up to 1 ounce (28.5 grams) of cannabis flower and up to 8 grams of concentrated cannabis products. Medical patients may be allowed to purchase more, depending on their needs.\n\n5. **Online Orders and Deliveries**: Many dispensaries offer online ordering with in-store pickup or delivery services. Ensure that the delivery service is licensed.\n\n6. **Consumption Rules**: Cannabis cannot be consumed in public places. Use is allowed in private residences or designated areas.\n\n7. **Growing Your Own**: California residents are allowed to grow up to six cannabis plants for personal use at home.\n\nAlways ensure that you are purchasing from a licensed dispensary and adhering to state and local laws regarding cannabis use and possession.",
